If anyone is curious, the "teeth" are actually called "cuts" or "bittings".  The part of the key that the key ring goes into is called the "bow" or "head".  The part where the bow meets the part where the cuts are is called the "shoulder".  The key Nate made is designed for a "Kwikset" brand of lock.  If you look at the bow of the key, you can see the letter "K", which stands for Kwikset.  It is a backwards K in most of the video though.  :)
